</gmd:CI_Citation>         </gmd:citation>         <gmd:abstract>           <gco:CharacterString>QuadIndex_Poly is a coverage which contains theoretically perfect quadrangle polygons encompassing the State of North Dakota. Attribution of the polygons includes 1:250000, 1:100000, 1:24000, and 1:24000 quarter quadrangle delineations, the dates of the 7.5', 1:24000 scale USGS topo maps, and the photo dates for the USGS Digital Orthophoto Quarter Quadrangles (DOQQs).</gco:CharacterString>         </gmd:abstract>         <gmd:purpose>           <gco:CharacterString>This coverage can be used in a variety of ways. It could be used as an index coverage for DLG availability, as an index to the dates of the topo quads and DOQQs, as a digitizing control coverage, or maybe as a clipping extent for clipping USGS Digital Raster Graphics and Digitial Orthophoto Quarter Quadrangles.</gco:CharacterString>         </gmd:purpose>         <gmd:credit>           <gco:CharacterString>North Dakota State Water Commission</gco:CharacterString>         </gmd:credit>         <gmd:status>           <gmd:MD_ProgressCode codeList="http://www.isotc211.org/2005/resources/codeList.xml#MD_ProgressCode" codeListValue="completed" codeSpace="ISOTC211/19115"/>         </gmd:status>         <gmd:pointOfContact>           <gmd:CI_ResponsibleParty>             <gmd:individualName>               <gco:CharacterString>Rod Bassler</gco:CharacterString>             </gmd:individualName>             <gmd:organisationName>               <gco:CharacterString>North Dakota State Water Commission</gco:CharacterString>             </gmd:organisationName>             <gmd:positionName>               <gco:CharacterString>GIS Coordinator</gco:CharacterString>             </gmd:positionName>             <gmd:contactInfo>               <gmd:CI_Contact>                 <gmd:phone>                   <gmd:CI_Telephone>                     <gmd:voice>                       <gco:CharacterString>701-328-4998</gco:CharacterString>                     </gmd:voice>                     <gmd:facsimile>                       <gco:CharacterString>701-328-3747</gco:CharacterString>                     </gmd:facsimile>                   </gmd:CI_Telephone>                 </gmd:phone>                 <gmd:address>                   <gmd:CI_Address>                     <gmd:deliveryPoint>                       <gco:CharacterString>900 E.         <gmd:lineage>           <gmd:LI_Lineage>             <gmd:statement>               <gco:CharacterString>Data developed by the State Water Commission.</gco:CharacterString>             </gmd:statement>             <gmd:processStep>               <gmd:LI_ProcessStep>                 <gmd:description>                   <gco:CharacterString>A fishnet grid was created with intersections at every 3.75 minutes of degrees latitude and longitude. Polygons were created, items added and attributed with USGS row and column information along with 1 degree x 1 degree block numbers being assigned. Through the use of INFO, this information was concatonated into the USGS naming conventions for 1:250000, 1:100000, 1:24000, and 1:24000 quarter quads. Names for the quads were taken from USGS index sheets or from existing data tables that the NDSWC had on hand.</gco:CharacterString>                 </gmd:description>                 <gmd:dateTime>                   <gco:DateTime>2001-08-01T00:00:00</gco:DateTime>                 </gmd:dateTime>               </gmd:LI_ProcessStep>             </gmd:processStep>             <gmd:source>               <gmd:LI_Source>                 <gmd:description>                   <gco:CharacterString>Theoretically perfect - Coordinates were derived from spreadsheet generated X's and Y's at a 3.75 minute of degree interval. Photo dates should be fairly accurate, however discrepancies have been found between source data paper files, photo headers, and CD covers. As updated photos are added, the photo dates will be more reliably transferred to this index.</gco:CharacterString>                 </gmd:description>                 <gmd:sourceCitation>                   <gmd:CI_Citation>                     <gmd:title>                       <gco:CharacterString>North Dakota Quadrangle Coverage</gco:CharacterString>                     </gmd:title>                     <gmd:date>                       <gmd:CI_Date>                         <gmd:date/>                         <gmd:dateType>                           <gmd:CI_DateTypeCode codeList="http://www.isotc211.org/2005/resources/codeList.xml#CI_DateTypeCode" codeListValue="publication" codeSpace="ISOTC211/19115"/>                         </gmd:dateType>                       </gmd:CI_Date>                     </gmd:date>                     <gmd:edition>                       <gco:CharacterString>1.0</gco:CharacterString>                     </gmd:edition>                     <gmd:citedResponsibleParty>                       <gmd:CI_ResponsibleParty>                         <gmd:organisationName>                           <gco:CharacterString>Rod Bassler - North Dakota State Water Commission</gco:CharacterString>                         </gmd:organisationName>                         <gmd:role>                           <gmd:CI_RoleCode codeList="http://www.isotc211.org/2005/resources/codeList.xml#CI_RoleCode" codeListValue="originator" codeSpace="ISOTC211/19115"/>                         </gmd:role>                       </gmd:CI_ResponsibleParty>                     </gmd:citedResponsibleParty>                   </gmd:CI_Citation>                 </gmd:sourceCitation>               </gmd:LI_Source>             </gmd:source>           </gmd:LI_Lineage>         </gmd:lineage>       </gmd:DQ_DataQuality>     </gmd:dataQualityInfo>   </gmd:MD_Metadata>
